title: Cherry-Evans, Graham in league WC 9s squad
text:
Manly captain Daly Cherry-Evans and South Sydney winger Campbell Graham have been added to the Australian squad for the Rugby League World Cup Nines in Sydney.

Cherry-Evans comes in after the withdrawal of Cody Walker (personal reasons), while Graham replaces injured Melbourne centre Curtis Scott.

The Australian squad will go camp on Tuesday.

The World Cup Nines will be played on October 18-19 at Bankwest Stadium.

AUSTRALIAN SQUAD (alphabetical):

Josh Addo-Carr, Melbourne; Jai Arrow and AJ Brimson, Gold Coast; Nathan Brown, Parramatta; Daly Cherry-Evans, Manly; Kyle Feldt, North Queensland; David Fifita, Brisbane; Tyson Frizell, St George Illawarra; Reuben Garrick, Manly; Campbell Graham, South Sydney; Wade Graham, Cronulla; Clint Gutherson, Parramatta; Ben Hunt, St George Illawarra; Mitchell Moses, Parramatta; Ryan Papenhuyzen, Melbourne; Kalyn Ponga, Newcastle.
